        <tr> 
          <td width="30">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="405" class="texte">
FULL TIME POSITION, Bordeaux France<BR><BR>(Experience in software integration required)<BR><BR>You will manage and motivate a team of engineers who are responsible for the integration of our ExEn gaming engine onto target Java Virtual Machines (VM) and mobile phone handsets.<BR>  <BR>Principle duties and responsibilities<BR><BR>·	You will be the main point of contact with potential and actual customers (VM vendors and Handset Manufacturers) for all project management issues.<BR>·	In line with company strategy, you will define and implement an industrial process for the integration of our technologies on to selected VMs and handsets<BR>·	You will be responsible for the successful completion of all integration projects. You will federate the internal teams, external contractors and the teams of our partners in order to respect the project objectives (milestones, deadlines, quality requirements…) <BR>·	You will coordinate, manage and increase the autonomy of the team of integration engineers you will lead internally (performance evaluation, career development etc….)<BR><BR>Education, experience and skills required<BR><BR>·	You have a Masters degree (or equivalent) in Computer Science <BR>·	You have experience in software integration in the telecoms industry (ideally mobile phone industry) and are familiar with the related industrial and technical constraints<BR>·	You have experience in both team management and project  management (at least 5 years experience)<BR>·	You have excellent communication skills ; you are proactive, open minded and an ‘ideas’ person<BR>·	You have strong leadership skills<BR>·	You have fluent written and spoken English and French<BR>·	Embedded Java knowledge will be a plus<BR><BR>If you are a flexible, proactive individual and you are eager to be a member of a very international team and contribute to the further growth of this highly international company (English is the working language), then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees. Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our best maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR><BR>
